Guidelines to follow

1. Use right datastructures for the given problem

2. write compact code

3. avoid creating unnecessary variables

4. avoid abbrevations as much as you can

5. descriptive function and variable names over code comments

6. don't be too clever, keep it simple

7. too much nested code kills code readability

8. consistent coding style and naming convention

9. organize code in multiple folders, files suitable to their purpose

10. using object oriented programming

11. use design patterns and architecture patterns

12.